The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and their structure, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of treewidth as a parameter and the focus on minor containment problems suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The use of planar graphs and topological minors suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category. The study of complexity and parameterized algorithms suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another possible category. Finally, the use of graph theory and combinatorics suggests cs.GT (Graph Theory) as a possible category.
